  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed -i '/usrbin_execdir/ s|/usr/bin|/usr/local/bin|' configure &amp;&amp;
./configure --exec-prefix= \
            --bindir=/usr/local/bin \
            --sbindir=/usr/local/sbin \
            --libdir=/usr/local/lib \
            --disable-static \
            --disable-kill &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--disable-kill</parameter>: This switch disables building the
        kill command that is installed in the util-linux package.
      </para>

    </sect3>

